In parallel, we are actively investigating options to increase the velocity of our recovery efforts. In order to ensure that we do not cause additional impact, we are proceeding cautiously but safely. During this time, customers can continue making changes but these changes will not propagate until we’ve fully mitigated this issue. We expect full recovery is a couple hours away.

source_payload.html: We can confirm errors for DNS resolution for some CloudFront distributions. During this time, customers may receive an NXDOMAIN response. Additionally, customers may also experience delayed propagation for changes to CloudFront distributions. We have identified the root cause of the issue and are actively working on multiple paths to resolving the errors. We have verified that our initial mitigation effort on a portion of the affected subsystem was successful, and we are actively working toward performing that mitigation across the fleet. We recommend customers continue to retry any failed requests while we work toward mitigation. A few services that use CloudFront distributions for delivering content may also be affected at this time.

'''Jill Zarin''' ({{née}} '''Kamen''') is an American television personality and businesswoman. She is best known as an original cast member on the [[Bravo (American TV network)|Bravo]] reality television series ''[[The Real Housewives of New York City]]'', in which she starred from 2008 to 2011.


==Early life and career==
==Early life and career==
Zarin was born in [[Woodmere, New York]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Jill Zarin |url=https://www.bravotv.com/people/jill-zarin |website=[[Bravo (American TV network)|Bravo TV]] |access-date=25 October 2023 |date=25 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Bessen |first1=Jeff |title=A 'Real NYC Housewife' in the Five Towns |url=https://www.liherald.com/stories/-a-real-nyc-housewife-in-the-five-towns,30475 |website=Herald Community Newspapers |access-date=25 October 2023 |date=2 February 2011}}</ref> to Saul and Gloria Kamen.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Fusaro |first1=Hannah |title=Jill Zarin Was Allegedly Blackmailed into Telling Ally Shapiro She Was Conceived by a Sperm Donor |url=https://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/jill-zarin-allegedly-blackmailed-into-telling-daughter-about-sperm-donor |website=[[Bravo (American TV network)|Bravo TV]] |access-date=25 October 2023 |date=27 March 2020}}</ref> She graduated from [[Simmons University]] in 1985 with a degree in retail management.<ref>{{cite web |title=Jill Zarin '85 Grows Fashion Brand from Handmade Masks |url=https://www.simmons.edu/news/jill-zarin-85-grows-fashion-brand-handmade-masks |website=Simmons University |access-date=23 October 2023 |date=9 March 2021}}</ref><ref name="Jill & Ally">{{cite web |title=About Jill |url=https://jillandally.com/pages/copy-of-about-jill |website=Jill & Ally |access-date=23 October 2023}}</ref>
Zarin was born in [[Woodmere, New York]]<ref name=":0">{{cite web |title=Jill Zarin |url=https://www.bravotv.com/people/jill-zarin |website=[[Bravo (American TV network)|Bravo TV]] |access-date=25 October 2023 |date=25 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Bessen |first1=Jeff |title=A 'Real NYC Housewife' in the Five Towns |url=https://www.liherald.com/stories/-a-real-nyc-housewife-in-the-five-towns,30475 |website=Herald Community Newspapers |access-date=25 October 2023 |date=2 February 2011}}</ref> to Saul and Gloria Kamen.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Fusaro |first1=Hannah |title=Jill Zarin Was Allegedly Blackmailed into Telling Ally Shapiro She Was Conceived by a Sperm Donor |url=https://www.bravotv.com/the-daily-dish/jill-zarin-allegedly-blackmailed-into-telling-daughter-about-sperm-donor |website=[[Bravo (American TV network)|Bravo TV]] |access-date=25 October 2023 |date=27 March 2020}}</ref> She graduated from [[Simmons University]] in 1985 with a degree in retail management.<ref>{{cite web |title=Jill Zarin '85 Grows Fashion Brand from Handmade Masks |url=https://www.simmons.edu/news/jill-zarin-85-grows-fashion-brand-handmade-masks |website=Simmons University |access-date=23 October 2023 |date=9 March 2021}}</ref><ref name="Jill & Ally">{{cite web |title=About Jill |url=https://jillandally.com/pages/copy-of-about-jill |website=Jill & Ally |access-date=23 October 2023}}</ref>

Upon graduating, Zarin became an assistant buyer at [[Filene's]] department store, and later the Vice President of [[Gold Toe Brands|Great American Knitting Mills]].<ref name=":0" /> In 2008, Zarin was announced as one of five women casted to appear in the [[Bravo network]] reality series, ''[[The Real Housewives of New York City]]'', the second installment Bravo's ''[[The Real Housewives|Real Housewives]]'' franchise.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Breaking News - Bravo Announces New Series "The Real Housewives of New York City" {{!}} TheFutonCritic.com |url=http://thefutoncritic.com/news/2008/01/14/bravo-announces-new-series-the-real-housewives-of-new-york-city-26434/20080114bravo01/ |access-date=2026-02-10 |website=thefutoncritic.com}}</ref> According to Jill, she was approached by a producer after they saw a picture of her, her husband Bobby, and her daughter Ally on the [[New York Social Diary]] website, and asked if she was interested in doing a reality show based on "glamorous [[Manhattan]] moms and their children," to which she agreed in order to expose her and her husband's fabric store, Zarin Fabric Warehouse.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Schawbel |first=Dan |date=March 6, 2013 |title=Jill Zarin: From The Real Housewives to a Successful Entrepreneur |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/danschawbel/2013/03/06/jill-zarin-from-the-real-housewives-to-a-successful-entrepreneur/ |url-status=live |website=[[Forbes]]}}</ref>


In 2010, Zarin published the book ''[[Secrets of a Jewish Mother]]'' with her mother and sister.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Zarin |first1=Jill |last2=Wexler |first2=Lisa |last3=Kamen |first3=Gloria |title=Secrets of a Jewish Mother: Real Advice, Real Stories, Real Love |date=15 April 2010 |publisher=Dutton Adult |isbn=978-0525951797}}</ref>
In 2010, Zarin published the book ''[[Secrets of a Jewish Mother]]'' with her mother and sister.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Zarin |first1=Jill |last2=Wexler |first2=Lisa |last3=Kamen |first3=Gloria |title=Secrets of a Jewish Mother: Real Advice, Real Stories, Real Love |date=15 April 2010 |publisher=Dutton Adult |isbn=978-0525951797}}</ref>

In 2011, Zarin, along with [[Kelly Killoren Bensimon|Kelly Bensimon]] and [[Alexandra McCord|Alex McCord]] were fired from the series.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2011-09-18 |title=Jill Zarin, Kelly Bensimon and Alex McCord not returning to "Real Housewives of New York City" - CBS News |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/jill-zarin-kelly-bensimon-and-alex-mccord-not-returning-to-real-housewives-of-new-york-city/ |access-date=2026-02-10 |website=www.cbsnews.com |language=en-US}}</ref>

In the fall of 2012, Zarin launched her jewelry line, Jill Zarin Jewelry Collection, which was sold at [[Macy's]] and [[Lord & Taylor]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=GLITTERRINGS |date=January 9, 2012 |title=Jill Zarin Signs Jewelry Licensing Deal with GLITTERRINGS |url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/jill-zarin-signs-jewelry-licensing-deal-with-glitterrings-136935063.html |url-status=live |access-date=February 10, 2026 |website=[[PR Newswire]]}}</ref>

In 2016, she launched Jill Zarin Home Rugs, an addition to her Jill Zarin Home collection, which includes Jill Zarin Home Furniture and Jill Zarin Home Tabletop and Accessories. The collection is sold in over 4,000 stores nationwide.<ref>{{Cite web |title=About Jill |url=https://jillzarin.com/pages/about-jill |access-date=2026-02-10 |website=Jill Zarin Home |language=en}}</ref>

In 2020, Zarin and her daughter Ally, founded the face mask company Shop Jill & Ally at the height of the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Our Story |url=https://jillzarin.com/pages/our-story |access-date=2026-02-10 |website=Jill Zarin Home |language=en}}</ref>

In June 2022, Zarin appeared in the [[Peacock (streaming service)|Peacock]] ''Real Housewives'' spin-off ''[[The Real Housewives Ultimate Girls Trip]]''.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2021-11-18 |title=‘Real Housewives Ultimate Girls Trip’ Season 2 Is Coming and It’s Got an Entirely Different Cast |url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/tv/a38272546/real-housewives-ultimate-girls-trip-season-2-cast-date-news/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211118210708/https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/tv/a38272546/real-housewives-ultimate-girls-trip-season-2-cast-date-news/ |archive-date=2021-11-18 |access-date=2026-02-10 |work=Cosmopolitan |language=en-US}}</ref> In 2024, she took part in the [[Amazon Freevee]] reality series ''[[The Goat (TV series)|The Goat]]'', where she was exiled in episode 10.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Downs |first=Stephanie |date=2024-05-09 |title='The GOAT' Stars Tease Dramatic and Competitive New Amazon Prime Reality Series (Exclusive) |url=https://popculture.com/reality-tv/news/the-goat-stars-tease-dramatic-and-competitive-new-amazon-prime-reality-series-exclusive/ |access-date=2026-02-10 |website=PopCulture.com |language=en-US}}</ref>

On February 3, 2026, Zarin, Luann de Lesseps, Ramona Singer, Kelly Bensimon and Sonja Morgan were all announced to star in the E! network docu-series ''The Golden Life''.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Whittock |first=Jesse |date=2026-02-03 |title=‘RHONY’ Stars Reunite On E! For ‘The Golden Life’ |url=https://deadline.com/2026/02/rhony-stars-golden-life-reality-series-1236707291/ |access-date=2026-02-10 |website=Deadline |language=en-US}}</ref> Seven days later on February 10, Zarin was fired from the series after posting an Instagram video criticizing [[Bad Bunny|Bad Bunny's]] performance at the [[Super Bowl LX halftime show|2026 Super Bowl]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Aurthur |first=Kate |date=2026-02-10 |title=Jill Zarin Fired From E!’s ‘RHONY’ Reunion Show ‘The Golden Life’ After Racist Bad Bunny Tirade (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2026/tv/news/jill-zarin-fired-rhony-reunion-the-golden-life-after-bad-bunny-video-1236657606/ |access-date=2026-02-10 |website=Variety |language=en-US}}</ref>
